Ahlrada Ahn|Spearbreaker	A mixed-blood warrior of Tiste Edur and Bluerose descent, known by the pseudonym Spearbreaker. He commands a company of warriors and serves among the Tiste Edur forces. Weathered in appearance with dark eyes, skin darker than pure-blooded Edur, and streaks in his long unbound hair, he is left-handed and bears a dramatically enlarged left wrist from constant weapon practice. Shadow wraiths characteristically swarm around him. Solitary and introspective, an outsider among his peers, he keeps his true thoughts and origins largely concealed while maintaining an admired command presence.<br>
Banaschar	A human male, once a priest of D'rek in the Jakatakan temple on Malaz Island, now an ex-priest turned wandering drunk. Middle-aged with even, benign features and dark hair worn in a queue between his shoulders, he is typically unkempt and seen in weathered leathers or tattered robes. He possesses a warren of Mockra magic that makes it difficult for others to remember his face after meeting him. Cautious and careful not to pry into others' histories, he carries a burden of guilt and determination beneath his degraded exterior.<br>
Barathol Mekhar|Barathol	A skilled blacksmith and former military officer of the Red Blades from Seven Cities. An imposing figure — huge in stature with deep onyx-black skin, dark eyes, military-style facial scarification, and hands and forearms bearing old blade-cut scars. Reserved and taciturn, he prefers anonymity and avoids drama, expressing a strong desire to live unnoticed. Despite his quiet demeanour, he demonstrates genuine compassion toward vulnerable individuals and lets his deeds speak louder than words.<br>
Chaur	A young man from a small hamlet in Seven Cities, ward and companion to the blacksmith Barathol Mekhar. Huge and well-muscled with pocked, monstrous features and skin resembling stained leather, he possesses the mind of a child — good-natured, mute, and fiercely devoted to those close to him. Despite his simple-mindedness he has genuine emotional depth, showing tender affection and childlike wonder at the world around him.<br>
Crump	A sapper in the Malazan 14th Army. Notably tall with a long horsey face, widely-spaced eyes, a scrawny neck, prominent ears, an oversized Adam's apple, and absurdly long legs with knobby knees and huge boots. Generally regarded as simple-minded, with a broad, mindless grin of gleaming teeth. He enjoys singing rambling, nonsensical swamp songs that irritate his squadmates and survives dangerous situations through luck rather than skill.<br>
Curdle	One of two spirits — the other being Telorast — imprisoned in a fragment of Kurald Emurlahn. They manifest as shades of translucent flesh with luminescent bones and skeletal faces with black-pitted eyes, and typically possess bodies to interact with the physical world. Curdle and Telorast maintain constant banter characterised by insults, threats, and deception, mixing dark humour with genuine menace. They share a history of thievery and demonstrate considerable cunning, though they frequently lie and obscure the truth.<br>
Dejim Nebrahl	A D'ivers T'rolbarahl of the First Empire, born when seven remaining T'rolbarahl imparted their souls into a human child. He exists in seven simultaneous reptilian panther-like forms of immense size — powerful arms, long-taloned hands, squat bony skulls, glistening black eyes with blood-red vertical pupils, needle-like fangs, and dark glistening skin. Deeply cunning and considered supreme among his kind, he harbours contempt for humanity and an abiding belief that his kind should have ruled. Driven by predatory hunger and strategic intelligence.<br>
Dunsparrow	Captain of the City Guard in Y'Ghatan, a human female from Quon Tali. Tall and handsome in a hard, unyielding way, with solid features, sun-darkened skin, and light grey eyes. She typically wears a chain vest beneath a plain Telaba garment. Resilient and strategically competent, she trains garrison forces in defensive tactics.<br>
Faradan Sort	A Malazan military officer commanding the 9th Company of the 8th Legion within the 14th Army, the Bonehunters. Tall and straight-backed with short-cropped hair and a Korelri accent, she carries a sword in a silver-traced scabbard. Stern, icy, and calculating, she prioritises results and military discipline and speaks sparingly. She demonstrates decisive tactical skill in crises and an emphatic intolerance for scorpions, which she crushes without hesitation.<br>
Futhgar	A corporal serving in Onearm's Host, the Malazan 5th Army. He carries a broad-bladed Kethra knife and a sticker. A dutiful soldier who follows orders from superior officers without question.<br>
Ganath	A Jaghut sorceress, tall and gaunt with greyish-green skin, long black hair worn in a single braid, amber eyes with vertical pupils, and tusks sheathed in tarnished silver that appear black. She wears a silver-clasped harness and an iron mail baldric hung with knives in copper scabbards. A powerful practitioner of ice magic and the Omtose Phellack warren. Pragmatic and world-weary, she has grown frustrated with certain long-standing conflicts and is somewhat unfamiliar with human customs despite her ancient age.<br>
Hayrith	An elderly woman residing in a small Seven Cities hamlet near Barathol Mekhar's community. In her youth she followed the Falah'd of Hissar's Holy Army across many battlefields, giving her substantial practical medical knowledge. She assists injured travellers and provides medical aid, and is direct and irritable when her expertise is questioned. Pragmatic and non-judgmental, with a sharp tongue and a habit of verbal sparring.<br>
Hellian	A soldier from Kartool, serving as sergeant commanding the 8th squad of the Bonehunters. Soft-featured with bright, always-wet lips, typically appearing dishevelled from her constant heavy drinking — a habit rooted in a deep phobia of spiders. Despite her inebriation she demonstrates surprising tactical competence and genuine care for her soldiers' survival. Sharp-witted and sardonic, her unconventional leadership style earns respect through results.<br>
Kulat	An elderly former goat herder from a small Seven Cities hamlet, companion to the blacksmith Barathol Mekhar. A bent old man typically wearing little more than rags, with a distinctive habit of sucking on three or more small black polished stones; his teeth are worn and chipped and his hands bear suppurating sores. Pragmatic and calculating, he is focused on accumulating personal wealth and power and is ultimately self-serving in his ambitions.<br>
Masan Gilani|Masan	A Dal Honese soldier in the Malazan 14th Army. Tall and dark-skinned with graceful long legs and elongated almond-shaped eyes, widely considered beautiful with a voice praised for its richness. Originally heavy infantry, she transitions to the marines and is noted as the best rider in her unit, skilled with long-knives and a hooked blade. Capable and composed, she maintains a maternal protectiveness toward younger soldiers and demonstrates independent judgement and emotional maturity.<br>
Noto Boil	Company healer and battlefield medic in Onearm's Host, the Malazan 5th Army. Originally from Kartool and once a priest of Soliel before departing the priesthood over disagreements with temple politics. Tall and stooped with long wispy colourless hair, tanned leather-like skin, grey eyes set in yellow-tinged whites, receded gums, and worn teeth — he habitually picks at them with a needle-sharp fish spine. Considered irritating by those around him but acknowledged as competent. He insists on being called by his full name, Noto Boil, and not simply half of it.<br>
Nulliss	An elderly woman of the Semk people living in a Seven Cities village alongside Barathol Mekhar. She serves as a healer in her community, possessing considerably more medical expertise than her modest reputation suggests. Outspoken and opinionated, she trades barbs regularly with the fellow villager Hayrith and is unafraid to challenge others directly or take charge in a crisis.<br>
Rythe Bude	A Fist in Onearm's Host, the Malazan 5th Army. Originally from Shal-Morzinn, she fled her homeland after crossing three sorcerer kings and eventually enlisted in the Malazan military, serving under Captain Kindly during the Nathilog campaigns. Dark-skinned with a round face, large dark luminous eyes, and naturally wavy black hair worn short. Loyal and principled, she demonstrates strong character in supporting command authority and maintaining the cultural traditions of her homeland.<br>
Samar Dev	A scholar, inventor, and witch from Ugarat in Seven Cities, in her early thirties. Skilled across multiple disciplines including chemistry, anatomy, geography, cartography, linguistics, and astronomy, she deliberately restricts the release of her inventions based on potential for misuse. Pragmatic and distrustful of philosophy, she combines intellectual rigour with ethical caution. Headstrong and self-reliant, she is not easily intimidated and speaks her mind with blunt directness.<br>
Sathbaro Rangar|Sathbaro	An Arapay Tiste Edur warlock serving as magical practitioner for the Third Edur Imperial Fleet under the command of Tomad Sengar. Elderly with a malformed body, a rasping voice, and one bent leg that causes him to hobble. Prone to dramatic emotional outbursts and dismissive of those he considers inferior, he wields Chaos sorcery and is tasked with opening mystical passages during military operations.<br>
Sweetcreek	A Malazan officer of Falari descent serving in Onearm's Host. She has wild red hair worn long, a pretty face, fair skin, and petite features. Professional and duty-focused, she is somewhat rigid in protocol and voices scepticism about leadership decisions she disagrees with, though she ultimately follows orders through the chain of command.<br>
Taralack Veed|Taralack	An outlawed Gral warrior, the sole surviving member of the Eroth bloodline, serving as an agent of the Nameless Ones. He has black swept-back hair, arcane tattoos swirling across his forearms, wary glittering eyes, and wears a hide shirt and hooded cape. Cunning and manipulative by nature, he is driven by ambition and a desire for personal vindication.<br>
Taxilian	An architect from Taxila who was captured while fleeing the Bluetongue Plague and pressed into service as an interpreter for the Tiste Edur. He bears tattoos on his forearms identifying his origins. Intelligent and resourceful, he purposefully sabotages language lessons by mixing dialects as a form of quiet resistance. Cautious about revealing his true name, and deeply curious about architecture and the mystical properties of geometry and spatial design.<br>
Telorast	One of two spirits — the other being Curdle — imprisoned in a fragment of Kurald Emurlahn. They manifest as shades of translucent flesh with luminescent bones and skeletal faces with black-pitted eyes, and typically possess bodies to interact with the physical world. Telorast and Curdle maintain constant banter characterised by insults, threats, and deception, mixing dark humour with genuine menace. They have a history of thievery and demonstrate considerable cunning, though they frequently lie and obscure the truth.<br>
Torahaval Delat|Torahaval	A woman from Seven Cities serving as Priestess of Poliel, goddess of pestilence. She has dark skin and long legs. Possessed of some magical ability, she is driven by a search for spiritual fulfilment, carrying a profound inner emptiness she seeks to fill through devotion.<br>
Touchy	A city guard in Kartool's Septarch District under Hellian, twin brother of Brethless and slightly older by a few minutes — a fact he insists upon. Hellian characterised the twins as hopelessly inexperienced despite their age. Neither can swim, and both tend to respond to orders in tandem, confusing those around them.<br>
Urb	A city guard corporal in Kartool's Septarch District under Hellian. Large and uncommonly handsome with a perpetually sad-looking round face. Loyal and protective, he proves reliable and dependable when called upon, showing particular devotion to keeping those under his command safe.<br>
Varat Taun	A Letherii military officer from the region of Bluerose, serving as second-in-command to Atri-Preda Twilight. He demonstrates pragmatic intelligence, observational skill, and principled restraint. A family man with a wife and daughter in Bluerose, separated from them by military service.<br>
